Owen Leonard and his sons Tom, 7, and Liam, 11, at Lattone Lough, Northern Ireland. “When I was a teenager and started to drive, I had friends on the other side of the border and to call to their houses you had to go through a British army checkpoint,” Owen said. “And I remember the first time going through and the soldier asked me where I was going, and I said I was going to Newtownbutler, and he asked me would I get him some beer and cigarettes.”
 
John Sheridan and his dog, Pip, in County Fermanagh, Northern Ireland. “We are promised that there’ll be no return to a hard border,” he said. “Well, what I want to hear is there’ll be no return to any border, not even psychologically, because there’s no such thing as a soft border.”
